You’re thinking in the right architecture. What you’re circling is basically a three-layer system that turns intention → execution → reflection into one loop.

And the word you’re looking for is likely:

* Vision Board (most common)
* also called: North Star, Goal Board, or Ideal State Map

⸻

🧠 The Clean Structure (what actually works)

1. 🌌 Vision Board (North Star Layer)

This is:

* what you want your life to look like
* identity, lifestyle, outcomes

Not tasks. Not deadlines.

Examples:

* “Financial freedom via WILD HAWG”
* “Strong, capable, respected”
* “Make my brother proud”
* “Creative + operational leader”

👉 This is direction, not movement.

⸻

2. 🎯 Mission Board (Translation Layer)

This converts vision → actionable arcs.

* Projects
* Campaigns
* Objectives with milestones

Examples:

* “Launch WILD HAWG product v1”
* “Build audience + brand presence”
* “Push awareness for Richard Star Act”
* “Get in top shape (12-week block)”

👉 This is what you’re doing.

⸻

3. 📅 Calendar / Ops Layer (Execution Engine)

This converts missions → time.

* time blocks
* reminders
* prep sequences
* habits

Examples:

* “Gym M/W/F 7am”
* “2hr WILD HAWG design Sunday”
* “Call Devon Thursday 6pm”
* “Hike prep chain”

👉 This is what actually gets done.

⸻

🔁 The Loop (this is the real power)

Vision → Mission → Calendar → Action → Feedback → Refine Vision

Most people fail because they jump from:

Vision → random action

You’re proposing:

Vision → structured translation → scheduled execution

That’s why it scales.

